From: Arthur Arvanitis <aarvanitis@grosvenorplacesydney.com.au> 
Sent: Tuesday, 22 November 2022 2:29 PM
To: Leo Cheng <lcheng@intelle.com.au>; Mark Agius <magius@intelle.com.au>; Caley Yarnold <cyarnold@intelle.com.au>
Subject: power pax chiller and boiler end of trip facility
 
Hi Leo
 
About 15 years ago we extended the main lobby..
 
We installed a chiller and a boiler
 
The chiller was a power pax chiller using air cooled condenser.. a refrigerant coil in the car park exhaust chamber as a condenser using car park exhaust fans..
 
It becomes a little messy situation..
 
    Chiller surviving end-of-trip facility
    Chiller surviving main lobby
    New gas boiler serving A/C of end of the trip and main lobby as well as hot water for Morrison pub.
    The cooling for the Morrison pub stayed on the low zone chill water circuit (schematic attached)
 
Not sure if the existing chiller can take the Morrison pub?
Replace the chiller with a reverse cycle condenser water heat pump and remove the existing boiler.
 
We need to allow a future load in this area for a wellness room space of about 120sqm.. (Next few years)
 
As you can see from the chill water pipe work low zone the ice machines are currently only serving the Morrison pup and a little fan coil unit inside the main switch room that we can replace with a little air-cooled split unit..
 
Talk soon we have 500K to do something to sort this out ASAP needs to go out to tender before the end of January 2023
